MOST RECOMMENDED(BEST PRACTICES):
    - CREATE DATABASE airbnb_db;
    - CREATE USER airbnb_user WITH PASSWORD 'xxx';
    - ALTER DATABASE airbnb_db OWNER TO airbnb_user;
    - ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO airbnb_user;
    - GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO airbnb_user;

FINAL HACK:
    - GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE airbnb_db TO airbnb_user;

    WHAT YOU JUST DID: You created:
        | Item        | Meaning          |
        | ----------- | ---------------- |
        | airbnb_db   | Database         |
        | airbnb_user | Database account |
        | password    | Authentication   |
        | privileges  | Access rights    |

NANO:
    Nano controls:
        - CTRL + O → Save file
        - ENTER → Confirm save
        - CTRL + X → Exit editor
    Break it down simply:
        - nano → a terminal-based text editor (used in Linux/Ubuntu servers)
        - config/settings.py → the file you want to open and edit

